http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/University-campus-team-wins-quiz/article13985078.ece

The team representing the University of Kerala’s Kariavattam Campus won the first prize of Rs.5,000 in the Professor Clement D’Cruz Memorial Inter-college Quiz competition organised by the Former Students’ Association of Fatima Mata National College here on Wednesday. The second prize of Rs.3,000 went to the team representing University College, Thiruvananthapuram, and the third prize of Rs.2,000 went to the team representing the host college. Charles D’Cruz, a former student and retired chemistry professor of the host college and son of Prof. Clement D’Cruz, gave away the prizes to the winners, a statement issued by the college here said. — Special Correspondent